Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setWhatIfPortPriority(25.10)                      setWhatIfPortPriority(25.10)

Name
       setWhatIfPortPriority  -  Command setWhatIfPortPriority is obsolete and
       has been replaced by setWhatIfTimingMode

Syntax
        setWhatIfPortPriority

       [-driveCell | -portParam]

       Command setWhatIfPortPriority is obsolete and has been replaced by set-
       WhatIfTimingMode.

       On output ports, parameters such as capacitance value, maximum  capaci-
       tance values, maximum transition value, or the maximum fanout value can
       come  from  the  driver (setWhatIfDriveType command) or they can be set
       through the setWhatIfPortParameters command.

       The setWhatIfPortPriority command defines which of  these  values  will
       take precedence in case of a conflict.

       You can use this command after the module definition of the blackbox or
       the blackblob is available with the I/O's in the Verilog netlist.

       Note: This feature is available only in the CTE mode.

Parameters
       -driveCell
              Specifies  that  the  values  set through the setWhatIfDriveType
              command will take precedence

       -portParam
              Specifies that the values set through  the  setWhatIfPortParame-
              ters command will take precedence.

       The default value is -portParam.

